# libversion-perl on older perl, or perl-modules from 5.10 has it
# included, same as libperl-critic-perl dependencies.  But have
# libversion-perl first in case that makes apt etc inclined to
# download that rather than upgrade perl.
#

Source: libperl-critic-pulp-perl
Section: perl
Priority: optional
Build-Depends: cdbs, debhelper (>= 4)
Maintainer: Kevin Ryde <user42@zip.com.au>
Standards-Version: 3.8.0
Homepage: http://www.geocities.com/user42_kevin/perl-critic-pulp/index.html
Bugs: mailto:user42@zip.com.au

Package: libperl-critic-pulp-perl
Architecture: all
Depends: perl (>= 5.6), libperl-critic-perl (>= 1.082), libversion-perl | perl-modules (>= 5.10), ${misc:Depends}
Description: Some add-on policies for perlcritic
 This is some further policies for perlcritic:
 .
  * ConstantBeforeLt -- avoid problems with "FOO < 123"
  * NotWithCompare -- avoiding problems with "! $x == $y"
  * ProhibitEmptyCommas -- consecutive commas
  * ProhibitNullStatements -- find stray semicolons
  * RequireEndBeforeLastPod -- __END__ before POD at end of file
  * TextDomainPlaceholders -- check args to __x and __nx
  * UnexpandedSpecialLiteral -- check __PACKAGE__ etc unexpanded
